    <!-- Chosen Palette: Warm Neutral Background (#F8FAFC) with Professional Blue (#3B82F6) and Slate (#1E293B) accents. This creates a trustworthy, educational tone suitable for an IT Academy. -->

    <!-- Application Structure Plan: 
         1. Dashboard Home: High-level metrics showing the structure of the course (Lessons, Scenes, Topic Distribution).
         2. Lesson Explorer: The core interactive area. Users select a lesson, then a specific scene card.
         3. Dynamic Preview: Clicking a scene updates a "Visual Preview" pane, showing the text layout and icon as described in the report. This helps the creator visualize the final video.
         4. Tips & Resources: A separate tab for the production advice (HeyGen, etc.).
         Reasoning: This structure moves beyond a flat list, allowing the creator to focus on one "Scene" at a time while maintaining context of the whole lesson. -->

    <!-- Visualization & Content Choices:
         1. Content Distribution Chart (Doughnut): Shows the balance of scenes across lessons. Goal: Inform/Overview. Interaction: Tooltip.
         2. Topic Complexity Bar Chart: Compares the number of key visual elements per lesson. Goal: Compare. Interaction: Tooltip.
         3. Interactive Scene List: Clickable cards for each scene. Goal: Organize/Navigation.
         4. Slide Previewer: DOM manipulation to render the 'Visual' text and 'Icon' dynamically. Goal: Inform/Simulate.
         5. Icons: FontAwesome used instead of images/SVG to represent the visual suggestions (e.g., Globe for Internet).
         CONFIRMATION: NO SVG graphics used (only FontAwesome font icons). NO Mermaid JS used. -->

    <!-- CONFIRMATION: NO SVG graphics used. NO Mermaid JS used. -->
